benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/tags - Add tags to bundle

covered: Valid POST payload flows demonstrate successful tag creation for a bundle using various header combinations (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC07)
Handling of invalid inputs and error conditions is well covered (TC08, TC09, TC10, TC11, TC12, TC13, TC15, TC18)
Authorization and access control scenarios are tested (TC13, TC16)
Resilience and failures are covered (TC17 service unavailable; TC19 recovery from transient network failure; TC22 timeout/slow backend)
Large payloads and limits are tested (TC20 maximum payload; TC21 payload too large)
Performance tests (TC24 normal load; TC25 peak concurrent load)
Integration scenarios (TC27 POST then GET; TC28 cross-service data consistency)
Data integrity and duplication considerations are addressed (TC26 duplication in response; TC06 existing vs new tags)
Security and input validation covered (TC18 malicious payload; TC23 extra headers)
gaps: Rate limiting tests are missing (throttling under high load)
403 Forbidden / insufficient permissions scenario not explicitly tested
Internal Server Error (500) scenario not explicitly tested
Explicit test for duplicate tag UUIDs within a single payload not covered
Edge case clarity around empty payload vs null payload not explicitly delineated
recommendations: Add a test for insufficient permissions (403) to complement 401 unauthorized tests
Add a 500 Internal Server Error scenario (e.g., simulated DB failure) to cover server-side failures
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure proper handling under high request volume
Add tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) for POST responses if applicable
Add a test for duplicate UUIDs within a single payload to confirm de-duplication/handling rules
Clarify and optionally test behavior for empty payload vs null payload and related edge cases
